   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Fifty-two WHERE SIN ABOUNDED GRACE HAS MORE ABOUNDED Scripture: Rom 5:20 Sin abounded Man is sinful and commits sins.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Man s sin is abounding.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Give a real example to prove how man s sin has abounded.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The older a man is, the easier it is for him to sin.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Grace abounded God not only has grace, but He has abundant grace.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The more our sin abounds, the more God s grace abounds.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>All of man s abundant sin needs to be resolved by God s abundant grace.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>How to receive grace and escape sin Although sin caused grace to abound, we should not continue to be in sin that grace may abound.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>We have to confess that we have sinned and should be punished for our sin, and that we need grace to save us.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>We should confess that we are bound by the power of sin and need grace to deliver us.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>We need to receive Jesus Christ and His salvation.</S>
   </TEXT>
